<plot>An impressionistic short film largely inspired by Andrew Wyeth's paintings "Christina's World" and "Helga", LEFT centers around the heartbreaking separation between a woman and the man she loves. Devoid of dialogue, this haunting and operatic film poetically reveals the grief of a woman trapped by the memory of her husband's departure in the midst of windswept grasslands.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?328301</url></doc>
